# .chezmoiignore
# Repo-only files that must NOT be applied to $HOME. chezmoi's default behavior of
# ignoring dotfiles at the source root is not something to rely on here — some source-root
# dotfiles (.chezmoi.toml.tmpl) are meaningful exceptions, so this file makes the
# repo-only/apply-to-home distinction explicit rather than implicit.

